  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong>-lined tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a good grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1723642042824-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1723642042824-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1723642042824-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1723642042824-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1723642042824-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>to a plate with a small pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>sugar</strong> and a good grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>quick-pickling liquid</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>cucumber</strong> into quarters lengthways</p><p>Add 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>cucumber quarter </strong>per person (you'll use the rest later!) to the <strong>quick-pickling liquid </strong>and set aside – these are your <strong>'gherkins'</strong></p><p>Tip: Turn the cucumber every now and then to make sure they pickle evenly!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1723642046096-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1723642046096-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1723642046096-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1723642046096-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1723642046096-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a small pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>sugar </strong>and a splash of<strong> cold water</strong></p><p>Cook the onions for 6-7 min or until they have softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1723642051934-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1723642051934-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1723642051934-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1723642051934-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1723642051934-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>meat-free hot dog sausage[s]</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), use<strong> tin foil</strong> to avoid mess</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20 min or until the sausage[s] are golden and cooked through</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1723642056218-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1723642056218-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1723642056218-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1723642056218-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1723642056218-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dice the <strong>remaining cucumber</strong> finely</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>diced cucumber</strong> to a pot over a medium heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 5-7 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, pour the <strong>pickling liquid </strong>from the 'gherkins' into the pot, add the <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and cook for a further 2-3 min or until all the liquid has been absorbed – this is your <strong>cucumber relish</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
